function App() {
  const { user, loading } = useAuth();

  if (loading) {
    return <LoadingScreen />;
  }

  return (
    <>
      {user ? <MainApp /> : <AuthScreen />}
    </>
  );
}

export default App;
```
That's the correct approach. Now the main app renders only when `user` is defined (logged in). Otherwise, `AuthScreen` is displayed.  And the loading screen covers everything when loading.

