The error **"Missing or insufficient permissions"** occurs because your **Firebase Firestore Security Rules** are currently preventing the app from writing to the `support_requests` collection.

By default, Firebase locks down all collections. You need to tell Firebase that authenticated users are allowed to "create" a document in that specific folder.

### 1. The Fix (Action Required in Firebase Console)
Go to your [Firebase Console](https://console.firebase.google.com/), select your project **"whats-my-credit-worth"**, go to **Firestore Database** > **Rules**, and replace your current rules with these:

```javascript
service cloud.firestore {
  match /databases/{database}/documents {

    // 1. Allow users to read/write only their own financial records
    match /users/{userId} {
      allow read, write: if request.auth != null && request.auth.uid == userId;
    }

    // 2. Allow any authenticated user to send a support request
    // But prevent them from reading other people's requests
    match /support_requests/{requestId} {
      allow create: if request.auth != null;
      allow read, update, delete: if false; 
    }
  }
}
```

### 2. Code Update
I've updated `ContactSupportModal.tsx` to detect this specific permission error and provide a clearer instruction to the user (or you as the developer) if the rules aren't set up yet.

